The Hotel Capri is 100 metres from Capri's famous Piazzetta, the main public transport services (bus, taxi, car park) and main public and private services(Congress Venue, cinema, night clubs, banks, Tourist Information Offices, and shops). The beaches are also within easy reach (Marina Grande and Marina Piccola are an easy 15 minute walk away or a 5 minute ride on public transport). The hotels restaurant offers traditional Meditterenean cuisine in a relaxed and welcoming atmosphere. The chefs specialties, all local produce, are complemented by a wide choice of local and national wines. The villa was built at the end of the 19th century. At the beginning of the 20th century the villa was turned into a hotel by the German baron Eduard Von Rahden. In 1920 the Arcuzzi family, from Anacapri, changed the name to Hotel Capri. In 1959 the Esposito family, acquired it and have been running it since then. The hotels continued commitment is to making you feel at home in our home.</Text></Description><Amenity><Code>Safe</Code><Text>Safe</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>AirConditioning</Code><Text>Air conditioning</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>MiniBarInRoom</Code><Text>Mini-bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Bar</Code><Text>Bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>TelephoneInRoom</Code><Text>Direct Dial Telephone</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Fridge</Code><Text>Fridge</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>BathRoom</Code><Text>Bath Room</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Restaurants</Code><Text>Restaurants</Text></Amenity><Rating><System>Stars</System><Score>40</Score><Description>Four star</Description></Rating><Rank>1</Rank></HotelElement>